{
  "stem": "20684.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's a simple recipe, but, you know, I wouldn't advise it to any other child to proceed.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, I don't find it all that beneficial.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, it was exciting, but I could give that a miss.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Never.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "None of us talked much about that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We just wanted to get on with-- with life.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A most unusual thing happened, as well.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Life wasn't all that boring for me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When we first got up to that camp, Stuttgart, in the displaced people's camp, where I for the first time started going to school, I was learning Hebrew because many of these children went to Palestine, were going to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In those days, it was Palestine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Orphans, most of them were orphans.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Some had families, but many were orphans.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Was those places-- well, we were with family.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Those-- some had family, some had orphanages were organized by Joint, which is an American organization, Jewish American organization-- funding.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were paying for those things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And an unusual thing happened.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because when I first come in with the children on the very first day that we went to school, we were given uniforms without any insignia.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were just brown uniforms.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when we went to school, people started throwing things at us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We couldn't work out what it was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "America was so naive.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were in the American zone in Stuttgart.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they weren't aware of the fact that those uniforms they gave us were old uniforms of Hitler Youth.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I thought it was funny I'd finish up with a uniform of Hitler.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Life can be funny.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So we-- we got out of the uniform very quickly and we just wore whatever clothes come from America.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I finished up with a fur coat.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
